The `atob()` function decodes a Base64-encoded string.

Remember that Base64 encoding will increase the size of your string by about 33%. Also, Base64 strings are not secure, so don't use them for sensitive data.

If you want a more compact encoding, you can use URL-safe Base64 encoding, which replaces unsafe characters (+ and /) with - and _ respectively. Here's how you can do it:

